OL,3,CDriver jailed after leaving pensioner
OL,4,Cwith facial fractures in road rage
OL,6,F"His actions provided a horrible
OL,7,Fexample of how quickly a road rage
OL,8,Fincident can escalate and how much
OL,9,Fdamage it could feasibly cause.
OL,11,F"In this instance, Hands appeared to
OL,12,Fcompletely lose control when the
OL,13,Fvictim criticised his standard of
OL,14,Fdriving.
OL,16,F"Despite his own child being in the
OL,17,Fcar with him at the time, he then
OL,18,Fproceeded to follow his victim, pull
OL,19,Fover, and ultimately punch him in the
OL,20,Fface.
